.TH "pskb_put" 9 "pskb_put" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pskb_put \- add data to the tail of a potentially fragmented buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" pskb_put
.BI "(struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *tail "  ","
.BI "int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
start of the buffer to use
.IP "tail" 12
tail fragment of the buffer to use
.IP "len" 12
amount of data to add

This function extends the used data area of the potentially
fragmented buffer. \fItail\fP must be the last fragment of \fIskb\fP -- or
\fIskb\fP itself. If this would exceed the total buffer size the kernel
will panic. A pointer to the first byte of the extra data is
returned.
